r’s philosophical and theological writings, most famously I and Thou, made significant contributions to religious and Jewish thought, philosophical anthropology, biblical studies, political theory, and Zionism. In this accessible new biography, Mendes-Flohr situates Buber’s life and legacy in the intellectual and cultural life of German Jewry as well as in the broader European intellectual life of the first half of the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aJewish philosopherszGermanyvBiography. 0aJewish scholarszGermanyvBiography. 0aZionistszGermanyvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Philosophers.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2019 Englishz978311061055008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2019z9783110606423oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065488240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300245233423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300245233.jpg  a978-3-11-061055-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065488-2  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-073776-9  DTL Humanities 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DPHb2019